    "slug": "5-online-strategies-to-encourage-recurring-giving",
    "link": "https://www.nptechforgood.com/2020/11/16/5-online-strategies-to-encourage-recurring-giving/",
    "title": {
      "rendered": "5 Online Strategies to Encourage Recurring Giving"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">By <span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\"><a style=\"color: #3b78dd;\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/lindsey-himphill-sandoval-335b8891/\"><strong>Lindsey Himphill</strong></a></span>, </span>Digital Marketing Strategist at <span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\"><a style=\"color: #3b78dd;\" href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/\"><strong>MobileCause</strong></a> <span style=\"color: #000000;\">\u00a0\u2013 a nonprofit technology company that pioneered text-to-donate and also offers an extensive suite of online, mobile, and event fundraising solutions.</span></span></p>\n<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Recurring donations are the most sustainable source of income for most nonprofit organizations. In fact, monthly donors donate <a href=\"https://philanthropynewsdigest.org/news/recurring-donors-440-percent-more-valuable-than-one-off-donors#:~:text=Recurring%20donors%20who%20give%20on,an%20online%20fundraising%20platform%2C%20finds.\"><strong><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\">440% more to charity over their lifetime than one-time donors</span></strong></a>. </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">However, without the right tools, many nonprofits will struggle to upgrade their one-time online donors into recurring donors. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">To address this, our team studied the campaigns of our top recurring giving customers within the <a href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/online-fundraising-software-2/\"><strong><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\">MobileCause platform</span></strong></a>\u00a0to identify some best practices and strategies. Take a look at some of the examples and strategies below for ideas for your own recurring giving campaigns.</span></p>\n<h2><strong>1) Set Recurring Donors as the Default Type on All Donation Forms</strong></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The easiest way to encourage more recurring giving from online donations is to set your </span><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\"><strong><a style=\"color: #3b78dd;\" href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/online-donation-forms/\">online donation forms</a></strong></span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>\u2019</strong> default donation type to recurring. Doing so will make donors aware that they can support your organization weekly, monthly, quarterly, yearly, etc. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">When making recurring donations the default donation type, lower the suggested donation amounts. New donors need to develop a deeper connection with your organization before donating larger amounts. It\u2019s better to get $120 over the year than $40 once.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-large wp-image-27651\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Homeless-Healthcare-Los-Angeles-recurring-donation-form-1024x768.jpg?resize=960%2C720\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"720\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Homeless-Healthcare-Los-Angeles-recurring-donation-form-scaled.jpg?resize=1024%2C768&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Homeless-Healthcare-Los-Angeles-recurring-donation-form-scaled.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Homeless-Healthcare-Los-Angeles-recurring-donation-form-scaled.jpg?resize=768%2C576&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Homeless-Healthcare-Los-Angeles-recurring-donation-form-scaled.jpg?resize=1536%2C1152&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Homeless-Healthcare-Los-Angeles-recurring-donation-form-scaled.jpg?resize=2048%2C1536&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Homeless-Healthcare-Los-Angeles-recurring-donation-form-scaled.jpg?w=1920&amp;ssl=1 1920w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>2) Create a Recurring Giving Pop-up</strong></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Contrary to popular belief, pop-ups do work! Nonprofits that use a pop-up asking a one-time donor to upgrade to a monthly donor achieve on average a <a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2018/09/20/5-must-know-recurring-giving-stats-for-nonprofit-fundraisers/\"><strong><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\">64% increase in monthly donations</span></strong></a>, yet only 14% of nonprofits use them!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Create a smart pop-up that targets one-time donors with a request to update to recurring giving. Within the pop-up explain the benefit of the recurring donation, such as how many meals, shoes, books, etc. it will purchase for your beneficiaries each month. With MobileCause, you can set the pop-up to only appear if a donation is below a certain amount (that you choose), so you can continue to bring in those large donations. You can also set the recommended monthly donation amount based upon the donor\u2019s original one-time donation (a percentage of it).\u00a0</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-large wp-image-27656 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Recurring_Giving_Pop_Up-2-1024x627.gif?resize=960%2C588\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"588\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Recurring_Giving_Pop_Up-2.gif?resize=1024%2C627&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Recurring_Giving_Pop_Up-2.gif?resize=300%2C184&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Recurring_Giving_Pop_Up-2.gif?resize=768%2C471&amp;ssl=1 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>3) Create a Membership Program</strong></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Memberships are an easy way to incentivize giving and involvement with your nonprofit organization. Monthly or annual membership programs encourage recurring giving by offering exclusive status, promotional swag, insights, or other incentives. You can encourage higher recurring giving amounts by establishing levels to the membership program with different perks to each level.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-large wp-image-27658 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Membership_Model_Infographic_Image-3-1024x683.jpg?resize=960%2C640\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"640\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Membership_Model_Infographic_Image-3-scaled.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Membership_Model_Infographic_Image-3-scaled.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Membership_Model_Infographic_Image-3-scaled.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Membership_Model_Infographic_Image-3-scaled.jpg?resize=1536%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Membership_Model_Infographic_Image-3-scaled.jpg?resize=2048%2C1365&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Membership_Model_Infographic_Image-3-scaled.jpg?w=1920&amp;ssl=1 1920w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>4) Segment Your Recurring Donors</strong></h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Be sure to recognize and celebrate your recurring donors in all communications. Create a segment of your recurring givers so you can send them specific and unique communications, appreciations, and updates. Doing so will prevent cancellations and encourage referrals from donors\u2019 friends and family. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Also, regularly thank and update your recurring donors on what their donations have enabled your organization to achieve. MobileCause\u2019s segmentation capabilities allows users to easily send recurring donors personalized </span><strong><a href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/text-messaging-for-nonprofits/\"><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\">text messages</span></a></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> and emails with the software.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/text-messaging-for-nonprofits/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-large wp-image-27660 alignnone\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/YMCA_Final_Membership_Renewal-3-1024x681.jpg?resize=960%2C638\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"638\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/YMCA_Final_Membership_Renewal-3-scaled.jpg?resize=1024%2C681&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/YMCA_Final_Membership_Renewal-3-scaled.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/YMCA_Final_Membership_Renewal-3-scaled.jpg?resize=768%2C511&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/YMCA_Final_Membership_Renewal-3-scaled.jpg?resize=1536%2C1022&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/YMCA_Final_Membership_Renewal-3-scaled.jpg?resize=2048%2C1362&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/YMCA_Final_Membership_Renewal-3-scaled.jpg?w=1920&amp;ssl=1 1920w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong>5) Automate Credit Card Expiration Reminders</strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.bluestate.co/news/stop-losing-recurring-donors/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\">Experts</span></strong></span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> estimate that two-thirds of recurring donations are canceled automatically (not manually) or when a credit card is canceled or expires. With MobileCause, donors receive expired credit card notifications via SMS (text) and/or email \u2013 on the date the credit card expires and 30 days prior \u2013 that link to a webpage where donors can update their new payment information. This feature enables you to reconnect with and maintain these important donors.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://go.mobilecause.com/create-recurring-donors-from-year-end-giving-campaigns-webinar-20\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-large wp-image-27663 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Credit-Card-Expiration-Reminder-from-MobileCause-1024x683.jpg?resize=960%2C640\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"640\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Credit-Card-Expiration-Reminder-from-MobileCause.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Credit-Card-Expiration-Reminder-from-MobileCause.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Credit-Card-Expiration-Reminder-from-MobileCause.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Credit-Card-Expiration-Reminder-from-MobileCause.jpg?w=1200&amp;ssl=1 1200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hopefully, these strategies and examples left you inspired to improve or create your recurring giving campaign. For more best practices and examples from real-world nonprofits, watch our on-demand webinar, </span><a href=\"https://go.mobilecause.com/create-recurring-donors-from-year-end-giving-campaigns-webinar-20\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\">Create Recurring Giving from Year-End Giving Campaigns</span></strong></span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\n<hr />\n<p>Launched in 2008, <span style=\"color: #3b78dd;\"><a style=\"color: #3b78dd;\" href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/\"><strong>MobileCause</strong></a></span> pioneered the use of text-to-donate in the nonprofit sector. In the years since they have expanded to offer online, mobile, and event fundraising solutions, peer-to-peer campaigns, mobile messaging, robust reporting &amp; analytics, and CRM integration.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://www.mobilecause.com/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-large wp-image-27667 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/MobileCause-Website-1024x596.jpg?resize=960%2C559\" alt=\"\" width=\"960\" height=\"559\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/MobileCause-Website.jpg?resize=1024%2C596&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/MobileCause-Website.jpg?resize=300%2C175&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/MobileCause-Website.jpg?resize=768%2C447&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/MobileCause-Website.jpg?w=1345&amp;ssl=1 1345w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" /></a></p>\n",
